ases (CoRoT-4b, 19b\nand 20b), transits that would have been lost for ground observations, due to\nthe large uncertainty in the previous ephemeris, have been recovered. The\nupdated ephemerides permit transit predictions with uncertainties of less than\n30 min for observations at least until the year 2030. No significant transit\ntiming variations were found in these systems.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 20 Dec 2021 13:55:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-12-21"}
